# Training Planner — Architecture & Coding Conventions

---

## Folder Structure

Strictly follow Next.js 14 App Router conventions.

```
src/
├── app/                          # All routes live here
│   ├── layout.tsx                # Root layout (fonts, global styles)
│   ├── page.tsx                  # / → Plan List
│   ├── plan/
│   │   └── [id]/
│   │       └── page.tsx          # /plan/[id] → Plan Detail
│   └── api/                      # API route handlers (when needed)
│       └── [...]/route.ts
│
├── components/                   # Shared UI components
│   ├── ui/                       # Restyled shadcn/ui primitives
│   └── [feature]/                # Feature-scoped components
│       └── PlanCard.tsx
│
├── lib/                          # Non-UI utilities
│   ├── supabase/
│   │   ├── client.ts             # Browser client (for Client Components)
│   │   └── server.ts             # Server client (for Server Components / Actions)
│   ├── types.ts                  # All shared TypeScript types and interfaces
│   └── utils.ts                  # Pure utility functions
│
├── hooks/                        # Custom React hooks (Client only)
│   └── usePlan.ts
│
└── actions/                      # Server Actions
    └── plans.ts
```

Rules:
- Never place business logic inside `app/` route files — keep pages thin, delegate to components and actions
- Never import server-only modules (`lib/supabase/server.ts`) inside Client Components
- `components/ui/` is only for restyled primitives — feature components go in `components/[feature]/`

