## Component Patterns — Server vs Client

Default to **Server Components**. Add `'use client'` only when necessary.

### Use Server Components for:
- Page-level data fetching
- Static or SSR-rendered UI
- Anything that reads directly from Supabase without user interaction

### Use Client Components (`'use client'`) for:
- Interactive UI: modals, expand/collapse, inline editing, drag interactions
- Hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRouter`)
- Event handlers (`onClick`, `onChange`)
- Real-time Supabase subscriptions

### Pattern — keep Client Components lean:

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component fetches, passes data down
// app/plan/[id]/page.tsx
export default async function PlanPage({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const plan = await getPlan(params.id)
  return <PlanDetail plan={plan} />
}

// ✅ Client Component handles interaction only
// components/plan/PlanDetail.tsx
'use client'
export function PlanDetail({ plan }: { plan: Plan }) {
  const [expanded, setExpanded] = useState(false)
  // ...
}
```

Never fetch data inside a Client Component when a Server Component parent can do it instead.

